1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with the impact of blur on recognition by convolutional networks, which is a core topic in computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of pre-trained models and fine-tuning to improve performance, which are common techniques in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as convolutional neural networks are a type of machine learning algorithm. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image processing and recognition, which are important topics in multimedia. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper deals with image artifacts and their impact on recognition, which is relevant to graphics.
